’. Compare   Sheehy  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Show","meanings":["English (Lancashire and Cumberland): probably a variant of   Shaw  , perhaps representing a blend in Middle English of Old English <i>sceaga</i> and Old Norse <i>skógr</i>, both meaning ‘wood’.","Perhaps an Americanized form of German   Schau  ."]},{"name":"Sheehy","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Irish Brendan, Aileen, Aisling, Brigid, Declan, Egan, Eoin, Finbar, Ronan.","Irish (Limerick and Kerry): shortened Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Ó Síthigh</b>, ‘descendant of <i>Sítheach</i>’, or <b>Mac Síthigh</b> ‘son of <i>Sítheach</i>’, a form of the Irish personal name <i>Síodhach</i> ‘peaceful’, from the adjective <i>sítheach</i> ‘peaceful’ or ‘other worldly’ (see   Sheehan  ). The noun <i>síth</i>, from which this adjective derives, means basically ‘settlement’, hence both ‘peace’ and ‘place inhabited by other world beings’. This name was established in Ireland from the early 14th century, when a branch of the Scottish McDonnells, descended from <i>Sítheach</i>, great-grandson of Domhnaill, settled in the country."]}]},{"name":"John","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["As a boy's name this represents a revival of Middle English <i>Jan</i>, a by‐form of   John  , or an adoption of the common European form with this spelling. As a girl's name it is a short form of names such as   Janet   and   Janice ."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705201,"age":67,"year":"1549","julianDay":2286821,"title":"Book of Common Prayer","description":"Book of Common Prayer, a product of the English Reformation, was published in 1549 for assistance in the administration of the sacraments and other rites and ceremonies of the church according to the use of the Church of England. The book outlined morning, evening, and communion prayers and orders for baptism and marriage, thus making England a truly Protestant state.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Book_of_Common_Prayer","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Book of Common Prayer","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705202,"age":76,"year":"1558","julianDay":2290108,"title":"Act of Uniformity","description":"The Act of Uniformity was passed by the Parliament of England and required all people to go to church once a week. The consequence of not attending church was a fine of 12 pence, which was a considerable amount for a poor person.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705205,"age":87,"year":"1569","julianDay":2294126,"title":"State Lottery","description":"A State Lottery was recorded in 1569. The tickets were sold at St. Paul's Cathedral in London.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"John Shaw was born in 1482, in Standish, Lancashire, England. He had at least 1 son. He died in 1581, in England, United Kingdom, at the age of 99."},"et":{"1482–1581":"1482–1581","1505–1586":"1505–1586","1569":"1569","1558":"1558","1586":"1586","1482":"1482","1581":"1581","1549":"1549","1505":"1505","Standish, Lancashire, England":"Standish, Lancashire, England","Lancanshire, England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1482–1581":"1482–1581","1505–1586":"1505–1586","1569":"1569","1558":"1558","1586":"1586","1482":"1482","1581":"1581","1549":"1549","1505":"1505","Standish, Lancashire, England":"Standish, Lancashire, England","Lancanshire, England":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1482–1581":"1482–1581","1505–1586":"1505–1586","1569":"1569","1558":"1558","1586":"1586","1482":"1482","1581":"1581","1549":"1549","1505":"1505","Standish, Lancashire, England":"Standish, Lancashire, Angleterre","Lancanshire, England":"Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"John Shaw est né en 1482, à Standish, Lancashire, Angleterre. Il a eu au moins 1 fils. Il est décédé en 1581, à Angleterre, Royaume-Uni, à l’âge de 99 ans."},"de":{"1482–1581":"1482–1581","1505–1586":"1505–1586","1569":"1569","1558":"1558","1586":"1586","1482":"1482","1581":"1581","1549":"1549","1505":"1505","